#### Government

*   [Ammar Campa-Najjar](/Ammar_Campa-Najjar), a candidate of Palestinian and Mexican heritage, ran as a [Democrat](/Democratic_Party_(United_States)) for Congress in 2020 to represent [California's 50th congressional district](/California%27s_50th_congressional_district). Campa-Najjar had previously served as a campaign official in San Diego, contributing to [President Barack Obama's](/Barack_Obama) reelection in 2012. His opponent in the 2020 election was Darrell Issa, also an Arab American with [Lebanese](/Lebanese_people), [German](/Germanic_peoples), and Bohemian ([Czech](/Czechs)) ancestry.

Only a select few Americans of Palestinian ancestry have served or are currently serving in the U.S. Congress. [Rashida Tlaib](/Rashida_Tlaib), born to Palestinian parents, is a Democratic congresswoman representing [Michigan's 13th congressional district](/Michigan%27s_13th_congressional_district) in the U.S. House of Representatives. She made history as one of the first Muslim women elected to Congress (alongside [Somali-American](/Somali-American) [Ilhan Omar](/Ilhan_Omar) of Minnesota) and is the first Palestinian-American woman to hold a seat in Congress. [Justin Amash](/Justin_Amash), a former [Republican](/Republican_Party_(United_States)) who later became an [Independent](/Independent_politician), is also of Palestinian ancestry and served in the U.S. House of Representatives for [Michigan's 3rd congressional district](/Michigan%27s_3rd_congressional_district).

At the state level, [Athena Salman](/Athena_Salman) serves in the [Arizona House of Representatives](/Arizona_House_of_Representatives) and is of Palestinian ancestry. [Iman Jodeh](/Iman_Jodeh), a Palestinian-American, was elected to the [Colorado House of Representatives](/Colorado_House_of_Representatives) in the [2020 United States elections](/2020_United_States_elections). [Fady Qaddoura](/Fady_Qaddoura), born in the [West Bank](/West_Bank), was elected to the [Indiana Senate](/Indiana_Senate) in 2020.

